@startuml
title System Sequence Diagram - Vessel Visit Execution Workflow

autonumber

actor "Logistics Operator" as LO
participant "System" as SYS

activate LO

' US 4.1.7 Create VVE
note right of LO : Vessel Arrival
LO -> SYS : Registers actual arrival of a vessel (Create VVE from VVN)
activate SYS
SYS -> SYS : Creates VVE (Status: InProgress)
SYS --> LO : Confirms VVE creation
deactivate SYS

' US 4.1.8 Update Berth
note right of LO : Berthing
LO -> SYS : Updates VVE with actual berth time and dock used
activate SYS
SYS -> SYS : Validates dock assignment
SYS -> SYS : Log discrepancy if dock differs from plan
SYS --> LO : Confirms update
deactivate SYS

' US 4.1.9 Update Operations
note right of LO : Cargo Operations
loop For each operation
    LO -> SYS : Updates execution of an operation (Start/End/Delay)
    activate SYS
    SYS -> SYS : Updates operation status
    SYS --> LO : Confirms update
    deactivate SYS
end

' US 4.1.11 Complete VVE
note right of LO : Departure
LO -> SYS : Marks VVE as Completed (provides unberth & departure times)
activate SYS
SYS -> SYS : Validates all operations are finished
SYS -> SYS : Updates VVE Status to Completed
SYS -> SYS : Locks VVE (Read-Only)
SYS --> LO : Confirms completion
deactivate SYS

deactivate LO
@enduml
